<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-41-0127 </DOCNO><TEXT>In addition to the cases published in literature, the authors add another10 cases of cavernous haemangioma or cavernoma which were removed surgicallyand confirmed histologically in the Neurosurgery Clinic of the HannoverMedical University between 1977 and 1985. This tumour is diagnosed withincreasing frequency since the introduction of cranial computerized tomography.Hence, cranial CT examination is indicated as the method of choice inthe diagnosis of these rare tumors.</TEXT></DOC>